Dimensional emotion psychologists see all emotions as motivational states that vary by arousal and valence and that are associated with activation of the broadly conceived appetitive (approach) or aversive (avoid) motivational systems. In contrast, discrete emotional psychologists argue that different emotions involve particular motivational action tendencies. By and large, the discussions of emotions in the following chapters will reflect the discrete emotion perspective
